snippet.textDisplay: Isn't the 20 vs 12gb thing more like a performance vs cost tradeoff?  I'd guess at 20gb the bus width of the card would match the regular 3080 whereas 12gb cards have the same bus width as a 3090.  I'm guessing the performance tradeoff simply wasn't worth it when you factor in the cost of the extra RAM in the price of these cards / profit for nvidia.  I'd be interested to see how this 20gb card actually performed in games compared to the 12gb version we got.  My assumption is the performance delta would be negligible for most applications / games. Especially considering the performance delta between the 3080ti and the 3090 it wouldn't surprise me if the card we got is actually a better performer in games, though that's just speculation.
